# API Keys for Free Services
# Get your free API keys from these services:

# OpenWeatherMap API (Free tier: 1000 calls/day)
# Sign up at: https://openweathermap.org/api
VITE_WEATHER_API_KEY=your_openweathermap_api_key_here

# IPGeolocation API (Free tier: 1000 requests/month)
# Sign up at: https://ipgeolocation.io/
VITE_GEOLOCATION_API_KEY=your_ipgeolocation_api_key_here

# OpenCage Geocoding API (Free tier: 2500 requests/day)
# Sign up at: https://opencagedata.com/
VITE_GEOCODING_API_KEY=your_opencage_api_key_here

# Guardian API (Free tier: 5000 calls/day)
# Sign up at: https://open-platform.theguardian.com/access/
VITE_GUARDIAN_API_KEY=your_guardian_api_key_here

# Note: The following APIs don't require keys:
# - Dev.to API (for tech/health articles)
# - Reddit API (for health discussions)
# - Hacker News API
# - REST Countries API
# - JSONPlaceholder API

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. The app will work with demo data even without API keys
# 4. News content is now sourced from multiple free APIs that don't require authentication